<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">

The formula area is located at the top of a table view, and displays formulas (if they exist) in a numbered list.

</FONT></P>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial"><B>

Resizing the formula area

</B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">

When you are not creating or revising formulas, you might want to reduce the formula area to see more of the table's information. 

</FONT></P>
<P><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="5" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR BGCOLOR="#fff8dc"><TD>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">

Drag the divider to hide the formula area completely, reduce its size or increase its size.

</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></P>
